The paper deals with the problem of online bipartite matching with edge arrivals, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also considers the problem in the stochastic framework, which involves probabilistic analysis and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses techniques from game theory (cs.GT) to analyze the competitive ratio of the proposed algorithm. Finally, the paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the auxiliary result.
